At least three people were confirmed dead and 39 others injured after a 10-storey building under construction collapsed in Kisii town in southwestern Kenya. The injured children were playing next to the building. Dozens of people, including construction workers, were believed to be trapped in rubble. Taken to hospital Several injured people were taken to hospital after the building collapsed at noon. The Kisii County Disaster Management team was leading the search for survivors. The building was next to RAM Hospital.   Conservationists say construction defied a court order halting the project. Regional bloc says its ready for action as reports of ceasefire violations rise.